source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010, 2023 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2023; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2022; (b) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses; (c) adjusted fertility using Brass P/F ratio method (or variants) with data on children ever born and births in the preceding 12 (or 24/36) months, both classified by age of mother, from the 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses; (d) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses and 2013 MICS. In addition, the (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2017; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) birth-histories data from the 1975-1976 WFS; (d) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2013 MICS; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1955-2010 Education Stats; (f) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1950, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses and 1975-1976 WFS have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) official estimates through 2010; (b) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2021; (c) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (d) adult deaths adjusted for underregistration using death distribution methods; (e) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) deaths by age and sex available from Register through 2021; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (d) maternal orphanhood from the 1975-1977 EDN and 1980, 1990 censuses and 2013 MICS; (e) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses and 1975-1976 WFS and 2013 MICS; (f) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (g) International estimates used up to 2021; (h) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1950-2010 Estimates and 2000 Census; (b) paternal orphanhood from the 2013 MICS; (c) indirect estimates of female adult mortality based on male widowhood data from the 1970, 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses and 1975-1976 WFS; (d) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) official estimates of infant and child mortality through 2017; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1975-1976 WFS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1980, 1990, 2000, 2010 censuses; (d) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2023; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1975-1977 EDN; (c) recent household deaths from the 1950-2017 Estimates and 2000 Census have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination (Latin American countries, Spain and United States of America); (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
